Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

Giving -1 because of the output when getting tags from namespace. I really don't like every single tag having a self reference, created at, and updated at.  The amount of data seems like overkill.  For a simple 4 character tag of "LAMP", you'd get back way too much data.  These KB add up, especially for responsive UIs that don't cache data. In the below, I think we need to have the returned tags be only the tags themselves (currently just a name, but perhaps a description later and parents / hierarchy).  See the spec for example body.

{"display_name": "My User Friendly Namespace DB Tags",
"description": "My DB Tags description.",
 "namespace": "OS::Tags::Databases",

  "updated_at": "2014-11-18T12:16:56Z",
